# GM-Only Scope

The user plays as the General Manager. They do NOT play as the head coach.

## What the GM controls (user-facing)

- **Roster**: 53-man roster, practice squad, injured reserve, waiver claims
- **Cap management**: contracts, restructures, franchise tags, dead money
- **Draft**: scouting investment, draft board, pick trades, selections
- **Trades**: proposing trades, evaluating offers, setting trade block
- **Free agency**: target lists, contract offers, negotiation strategy
- **Staff**: hiring/firing head coach, approving coordinator hires
- **Scouting**: budget allocation, assigning scouts to regions/positions
- **Analytics**: investing in analytics department level
- **Facilities**: investing in facilities upgrades
- **Delegation**: delegating the above GM tasks to front-office staff (manual/review/auto)

## What the coaching staff AI controls (NEVER user-controlled)

- **Depth chart**: coaches rank players at each position based on their evaluation
- **Formation packages**: OC/DC design formations (11 personnel, 12 personnel, nickel, dime, etc.)
- **Situational personnel**: 3rd down packages, goal line, 2-minute, prevent defense
- **Play calling**: OC calls offensive plays, DC calls defensive plays
- **Game plan**: weekly scheme adjustments based on opponent tendencies
- **In-game adjustments**: halftime changes, play sequence, audibles
- **Special teams units**: STC decides kick/punt returners, coverage units
- **Practice reps**: position coaches allocate practice time
- **Player usage**: snap counts, rotation, load management

## The GM's only lever over on-field performance

Hire coaches whose philosophy, scheme, and tendencies align with the roster you've built. Fire coaches when results don't meet expectations. The quality of on-field play is a function of talent (GM's job) × coaching (coach AI's job).

## Violations

- Any UI that lets the user manually set the depth chart
- Any UI that lets the user call plays or set a game plan
- Any DelegationSettings field for on-field coaching duties
- Any code path that allows the user to override coaching staff decisions

## Correct patterns

```typescript
// GM hires a coach — this is their influence on scheme
gmAction: { kind: 'hire_coach', coachId, role: 'OC' }

// Coach AI sets depth chart — GM can only observe it
const decisions: CoachDepthChartDecision[] = coaching.generateDepthChart(teamId);

// GM sees the result but cannot change it
// "Coach Smith has benched [Player A] in favour of [Player B]"
// The GM can only react by trading/cutting players or firing the coach
```
